				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Before you try pulling a lvl 65 high risk....<a name="32825"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 4 04 10:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Steppy's guide to pulling LDoN hard remains a terrific resource on this subject and is found in the guide section of EQDiva.
<br />

<br />
As to armor and AAs, my experience is that defensive AAs are particularly helpful, but that one does not need VT quality gear or better to pull a high risk LDoN.  I have been pulling high risk LDoN without any such gear.  Resists are important, especially magic resistance above 100, but Tak/Mir quality armor will suffice for pulling high risk LDoN.  
<br />

<br />
Moreover, the equipment upgrades from named drops will be helpful in continuing to pull.
<br />

<br />
A good thread on TCH:  <a target="_new" href="http://pub147.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallontour.showMessage?topicID=307.topic">http://pub147.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallontour.showMessage?topicID=307.topic</a></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
