				<td colspan="2"><span>My first couple of hard ldon were failures as I had resists on lull.  After chatting with another bard she said the most important thing was max charisma so you don't get resists on lull and of course FM.
<br />

<br />
I then worked hard to get planar power AA until my stats could go to 305.  A few charisma augments and a shammy buff later and my charisma was about 270 I think (I forget exactly).  That is usually enough to make sure the lull lands, but if pulling from a very full room I sing charisma song to get to 305 just for insurance before I get close <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  - no point getting pulped by six mobs in the hallway if you don't need to.
<br />

<br />
Never had a problem since then.
<br />
(well except for a Tak adventure where I was puller and CC and there was a room with TEN mobs in it, all close and four of them near the door.  Tried a few times and just couldn't do it - if we had an enchanter would have been ok - I could have brought four back with me<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> )</span></td>
